   public static int countdigits(int n){  // ‚ùå Not allowed here


your code has a method declared inside another method, which is not allowed in Java.

In Java, you cannot define a method inside main() or any other method. All methods must be declared at the class level.

-----------------

import java.util.*;
public class Test{
    public static void main(String args[]){
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.println("Please enter the number n");
        
        int n=sc.nextInt();
        System.out.print(countdigits(n));
            }
       
   public static int countdigits(int n){
            
            if(n==0){
                return 1;
            }
             int count=0;
            while(n!=0){
                n=n/10;
                count++;
                }
            return count;
            }
            
}   
